MULTICLASS MULTICLASSING

Multiclassing is the ability to level in all four guilds. Your ability to
level in other guilds than your prime guild is determined by your level
in your prime guild. You can multiclass into differant guilds at these 
levels: 30, 45, 60. Leveling in other guilds than your prime guild requires
gold as well as experience.

See Also : PRIME, LEVEL, GAIN, GRANDMASTER
#
PRIME

Your prime class is the class that you start in first. It is chosen when you
first create you character.
See Also : MULTICLASSING
#
MASTER GRANDMASTER

Once you have reached they level of 60 in a guild you are said to have Mastered
this guild.

Example: [ { 0 60  0  0} ] Tom Bombadil the Master Warrior

Once you have reached level 60 in all guilds you are said to have achieved the
status of GrandMaster. At this point you will be extremely strong and probably
have attained much respect from the other playeres. Once you become a grandmaster
you can then obtain 50 more levels.  You gains are based on your prime class.  Also
The price in experience and gold is standardized at 2,000,000,000 xp and 500,000,000
gold per GM level.


Example: [GM:    1    :GM] Tom Bombadil the GrandMaster



See Also: ULTIMATE, MULTICLASSING
